name: I've Got My Love to Keep Me Warm
Picture
comments: Rock re-recorded his song for radio with a different female vocalist, alternative country singer Moorer. Rock's label, Atlantic, was initially unable to get the rights from Crow's label to release the album version as a single. When the Moorer version was released, some mainstream radio stations began playing the Crow version, while country music stations played the Moorer version. As a result, Billboard credited the song to Kid Rock featuring Sheryl Crow or Allison Moorer.
